## Git commits

- Use **Conventional Commits**: `type(scope): description`.
- Valid types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `test`, `chore`, `style`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`.
- Scope: package name without `alpine-` prefix (e.g. `theme`, `sidebar`, `overlay`).
- Keep the first line under ~72 characters; use the body for extra detail if needed.

## Pull requests

- **Title**: Use Conventional Commits format — `type(scope): description`.
- **Description**:
  - **Summary** — What changed, 1–3 sentences.
  - **Changes** — Bullet list by area (e.g. stores, directives, tests, docs).
  - **Test Plan** — `pnpm test`, `pnpm run lint`, `pnpm run typecheck` must pass before requesting review.
  - **Checklist** — Linked issue, conventional commits, docs updated, changeset added, no AI attribution.

## Before finishing any change

```bash
pnpm test
pnpm run lint
pnpm run typecheck   # when types changed
```
